                "tagline": "Computational package for Low Energy Electron Diffraction",
                "description": "I developed and maintained an open source C based project for the computational calculation of low energy electron diffraction in collaboration with Prof. Georg Held, which compares theoretical models to experimental data. The original code base consists of a number of legacy programs developed by different authors spanning a period of almost 20 years and I have therefore spent considerable effort unifying and modernising the source code to better adhere to best practices and standards, whilst also leveraging open source libraries, such as GSL, libtiff, Cairo, and BLAS/Lapack. As part of turning the original programs into a fully-fledged open source project, I have placed the code under Git revision control, produced documentation using Doxygen, created cross-platform builds using the CMake makefile generator/packaging tool, as well as gained experience debugging with GDB. There is an aim of producing a user-friendly GUI/UX using Python/Qt.",
